# Project images — manual renames (do not auto-rename)

## Owner default: no auto `hero`

When ingesting or normalizing loose `IMG_*` photos, assign only **`before`**, **`after`**, and **`WIP-###`** sorted by **capture time**. **Do not** auto-create **`hero.jpeg`** from a WIP — the owner names `hero` manually when they want that shot on the story page and gallery tile.

- **`normalize-project-media-names.mjs`** — default is **no hero**; use **`--hero`** only if the owner explicitly asks to promote one.
- After normalize or a mistaken auto-hero: fold `hero` into the WIP sequence by capture time, delete the `hero` filename, then **`sync-project-story-images.mjs`** (page hero falls back to **`after` → WIP-001 → `before`**).

When the owner says they **updated / renamed images**, **reordered WIPs**, or **renamed files manually** in `projects/<folder>/`:

## Do

1. **Read filenames on disk** (`before`, `after`, `hero`, `WIP-###.jpeg` / `.png` only).
2. **Update HTML only** so story pages match those names:

```bash
node scripts/sync-project-story-images.mjs <id> [id …]
```

That syncs **`index.html`**: Work in progress gallery + project-hero + Open Graph — **no file moves**.

3. Optionally run **`publish-webpage.mjs`** for optimize / validate / meta — it does **not** rename files, but prefer **`sync-project-story-images.mjs`** when the only change is manual renames (faster, no image processing).

4. `node scripts/sync-projects-gallery-index.mjs <id>` — updates `data/projects-index.json` and rebakes the tile in `projects/index.html`.

5. If the project has numeric **`importance`** in `config.json` (home highlight lead or tile), also run **`node scripts/sync-home-highlights.mjs`** — baked `index.html` highlight images/descriptions do not update automatically. Shortcut after image-only changes: run steps 2–4 for the id(s), then `node scripts/sync-home-highlights.mjs` once to refresh all highlight slots.

## Do not

- **Do not** run **`normalize-project-media-names.mjs`** unless the owner **explicitly** asks to auto-rename loose photos by capture time.
- **Do not** promote a WIP to **`hero.jpeg`** or renumber WIPs to fill gaps — that script’s job, not “update images after my rename”.
- **Do not** assume “update images” means normalize + full publish.

## Wrong vs right

| Owner intent | Wrong | Right |
|--------------|-------|-------|
| “I renamed the files” | `normalize-project-media-names.mjs` then `publish-webpage.mjs` | `sync-project-story-images.mjs` |
| “Update images on the page” (after manual folder edit) | Renumber WIPs / create `hero.jpeg` from a WIP | Sync HTML from disk |
| USB ingest / messy loose `IMG_*` files | normalize + auto `hero` | `normalize-project-media-names.mjs` **only when asked** — **WIP by time, no hero** unless `--hero` |
| Agent scaffolded new project from USB | promote mid-sequence shot to `hero` | `before` / `after` + `WIP-001…` by capture time only |

## Page hero

Story hero / OG use files on disk: **`hero` → `after` → first `WIP-###` → `before`**. **`hero` is owner-only** — rename a file to **`hero.jpeg`** yourself when you want it; agents must not pick or promote one during ingest/normalize.
